Phase 7 #11 — user picks from queued candidates (Socket.IO realtime foundation live since Phase 7 #8e; client-side socket-client provider + useSocket hook live since Phase 7 #10; nodemailer HIGH CVE mitigation locked in #9 + enforcement repaired in #10; JWT carries organizationSlug; middleware enforces URL↔session match; coverage gate live since Phase 7 #5; per-user 24h reset cap live since Phase 7 #6; TDD mandatory per Rule 25)

Phase 7 #10 (socket-client) shipped on 2026-05-17:
- Tier 1 single-session (~30K Opus context). User picked (socket-client) from the recommended-next slot.
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/socket/client.ts` — pure factory `createSocketClient(opts)` wrapping `socket.io-client`'s `io()` with `withCredentials:true` so the Auth.js cookie flows cross-origin from APP_PORT=43512 to SOCKET_PORT=43515.
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/socket/session-invalidation.ts` — pure handler subscribing to the server-emitted `session:invalidated` event from the Phase 7 #8e-2 60s revalidation loop. Returns a disposer. Node-testable (no React import).
- NEW `apps/web/src/lib/socket/socket-context.tsx` — "use client" SocketProvider composing factory + handler with `useRouter().push("/login") + .refresh()` as the invalidation callback. Exports `useSocket()` (throws if outside provider) and `useSocketOptional()` (returns null).
- NEW client.test.ts (6 cases) + session-invalidation.test.ts (4 cases) — 10 RED→GREEN cases proving the contract end-to-end in node env (jsdom not installed, so React component tests are out of scope; the Provider's testable behavior lives entirely in the two pure modules per the [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]]).
- MODIFIED `types.ts` — added `session:invalidated` to ServerToClientEvents (server already emits it at apps/web/src/server/socket/revalidation.ts:77).
- MODIFIED `apps/web/src/app/app/layout.tsx` — wrap children in `<SocketProvider>` so every authenticated page under /app/* can consume `useSocket()`.
- ALSO FIXED two pre-existing regressions caught by #10's `pnpm build` validation pass:
  (a) Phase 7 #8e build break: webpack statically analyses dynamic-import string literals in instrumentation.ts for BOTH Node AND Edge graphs regardless of runtime gates. Edge has no `http`/`crypto`/`path`. Fixed by Edge-runtime webpack alias in next.config.ts: `config.resolve.alias = { ..., "socket.io": false, "@/server/socket/server": false, "@/server/socket/revalidation": false }` + `config.resolve.fallback = { http: false, https: false, crypto: false, path: false }`.
  (b) Phase 7 #9 audit-threshold false claim: pnpm 10's `pnpm audit` doesn't honor `.npmrc audit-level` for its exit code. Restored `--audit-level=critical` CLI flag in ci.yml. `.npmrc` kept as human-readable documentation.
- Test suite 75→85 (+10). pnpm build ✓ 27 routes (was failing on main since #8e). pnpm audit --audit-level=critical ✓ exit 0 (was exit 1 on main since #9). pnpm typecheck ✓ 0. pnpm lint ✓ 0 errors (1 pre-existing root-layout warning unchanged). Two-stage review (Rule 25) PASS.
- 3 new lessons: 🔴 [[pnpm10-audit-level-ignored]], 🔴 [[instrumentation-edge-stub-required]], 🟤 socket-client provider pattern (pure factory + pure handler + thin React shell — extends [[pure-helper-extraction-pattern]] to React-incompatible test environments).
- Squash SHA: `9d21461`. Closes (socket-client). Unblocks all real-time features that need a client socket — starting with (presence).

