  - smoke-test /forgot-password + /reset-password/[token] — public routes, no credentials needed (Phase 7 #4 carryover). With the 24h cap live, manual /forgot-password smoke for the same email is limited to 5 requests per 24h — use distinct emails or trust test assertions
  - smoke-test subdomain routing (Phase 7 #7c carryover) — edit /etc/hosts with `acme.localhost` / `evil.localhost`, OR use the /t/{slug} path pattern. Log in as user with org "acme" → visit http://localhost:43512/t/evil/app → confirm redirects to /t/acme/app. Super-admin → visit /t/evil/superadmin/users → confirm allows (option C bypass); visit /t/evil/app → confirm redirects to own subdomain
  - smoke-test Socket.IO handshake + session:invalidated event (Phase 7 #8e + #10 carryover). (1) start dev env with SOCKET_PORT=43515; (2) `curl http://localhost:43515/socket.io/` returns Socket.IO handshake page; (3) browser session in /app connects to ws://localhost:43515 + console logs no errors; (4) trigger session invalidation in another tab (sign out, or admin disables user) → wait ≤60s → verify the connected socket receives `session:invalidated` event AND the tab redirects to /login automatically.
